17/06/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A three-day conference of the chiefs of Southeast European countries' police forces began in Banja Luka on Wednesday (16 June). 
The forum, which is being held behind closed doors, is aimed at drafting concrete measures against organised crime, as well as activities to detain war crimes indictees.
In other news, Republika Srpska Interior Minister Radomir Njegus said Wednesday that Interpol BiH has launched 400 searches for Croatian Serbs indicted for war crimes. 
He added that, on the basis of Zagreb's request, police have apprehended one person. 
(Nezavisne novina - 17/06/04)
